  Main     Team     Blog     2014     2015  

   

   

Emilia Broman

Emilia studies bioinformatics at Aalto University. She minors in product development, and is also our resident graphic designer and photographer.

Hele Haapaniemi

Hele has a bachelor's degree in chemical technology, majoring in bio- and food sciences. She's currently doing her masters in the Biosystems and biomaterials engineering program at Aalto University.

Saara Hiltunen

Saara studies bioinformatics and molecular biosciences at Aalto. She has some practical work experience as a tutor in her guild.

Rashad Ismayilzada

Rashad studies bioinformatics at Aalto University. He has been shifting from computer science towards biology, led by a fascination for the life sciences.

Antti Koistinen

Antti is a master's student of chemical technology at Aalto University. He's minoring in biotechnology, so he knows his stuff.

Laura Laiho

Laura, our team captain, is a third-year student of molecular biosciences. She is also the chairman of a student organization at the University of Helsinki, so we are in good hands.

Nidia Obscura

Nidia, an energetic mathematician from Mexico, is studying for her master's thesis in the University of Helsinki. Her interest in biology stems from a wish to understand more deeply the applications of her research in practice.

Pihla Savola

Pihla, one of our younger members, has already been working in a research lab for a year. She's definitely a hard worker.

Snehadri Sinha

Snehadri is a master's student of molecular biosciences at the University of Helsinki. He's worked in a research team during his undergraduate years, so he knows his lab work.

Jami Valorinta

Jami is a bachelor's student of mathematics at the University of Helsinki. He likes all sorts of technology, and is our resident mad scientist -- or mad programmer in this case.
